no.motif.iter

Class PreIndexedContentIterator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • no.motif.iter.ReadOnlyIterator<T>
      • no.motif.iter.PreIndexedContentIterator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CharsInStringIterator

    public abstract class PreIndexedContentIterator<T>
extends ReadOnlyIterator<T>
    Base implementation for iterating over elements retrieved using an incrementing index, where the start and end indexes are known beforehand. E.g. characters of a String, or elements of an array.

        protected abstract T elementAt(int index)
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the element to yield. Guarantied to never be out of bounds with respect to the start and end indexes. E.g. if the given start and end indexes are 0 and 4, this method will be called for each of the indexes 0, 1, 2, and 3.
        Returns:
        The element for the given index.
